---
import SectionHeader from '../ui/SectionHeader.astro';
---

<section class="py-20 lg:py-24 bg-brand-softBg">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <SectionHeader
      title="What We Believe About Online Learning"
    />

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-brand-border/50 hover:border-brand-primary/20 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-primary mb-3">1. Knowledge needs structure</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-textMain">A good course is more than information. It needs order, outcomes, resources, and a mapped learner journey.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-brand-border/50 hover:border-brand-primary/20 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-primary mb-3">2. Learners need clarity</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-textMain">Students should know exactly where to start, what to do next, and how to successfully complete the learning experience.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-brand-border/50 hover:border-brand-primary/20 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-primary mb-3">3. Platforms should support the course</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-textMain">Kajabi, LMS platforms, and course websites work best when the underlying content structure is clear first.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-brand-border/50 hover:border-brand-primary/20 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-primary mb-3">4. AI should support humans, not replace them</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-textMain">AI can speed up planning and content production, but the final learning experience should always be human-reviewed.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-brand-border/50 hover:border-brand-primary/20 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-primary mb-3">5. Launch systems matter</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-textMain">Funnels, emails, checkout pages, onboarding, and ongoing support help turn a course into a working learning business.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-brand-border/50 hover:border-brand-primary/20 transition-colors">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-primary mb-3">6. Courses need improvement after launch</h3>
        <p class="text-brand-textMain">Learning systems are not 'set and forget'. They should be tested, updated, maintained, and improved over time based on feedback.</p>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
